
[1]drab

   DRAB, n.

   1. A strumpet; a prostitute.

   2. A low, sluttish woman. [This seems to be the sense in which it is
   generally used in New England.]

   3. A kind of wooden box, used in salt works for holding the salt when
   taken out of the boiling pans. Its bottom is shelving or inclining that
   the water may drain off.

                 DRAB, n. [L.] A kind of thick woolen cloth.

          DRAB, a. Being of a dun color, like the cloth so called.

                   DRAB, v.i. To associate with strumpets.
